Visiting https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/Dashboard.jspa, there are 100 separate http requests required to load the page. ~37 of these requests are javascript files. Most of these javascript files could be combined into a single requests.
For visitors with high latency connections, it takes an unreasonably long time before the page load is completed. By reducing the number of require requests, perceived performance will improve.
Note: I'm using jira.atlassian.com as an example, as this is not a problem specific to our instance(s) of Jira, but a more general issue with Jira as a product. We have several remote offices and JIRA performance is noticeably degraded for these offices.

