It would be very useful to have a means to link directly to a previous comment.  This is been raised a few time in past issues here: see for instance  ["Easy way of linking from one comment to another"|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-19537] , or ["Provide a way to link a comment to another issue's comment"|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-28976] ; but the replies tend to be rather terse "we will not be implementing this".

So I wonder: Can you perhaps suggest, as the developers, how users should meet this need? Ie, when you need to refer someone to a previous post (one, for instance, that might be too long to quote), what is the best approach?
